<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept//EN" "concept.dtd">
<concept id="concept_9588E880E0C7438E8B29AC7685AD0346"> 
  <title>Define a composite audience using rules</title> 
  <shortdesc>This article describes how to create a composite audience defined
	 by two rules. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <prolog> 
	 <metadata> 
		<othermeta name="solution" content="Marketing Cloud"/> </metadata>
  </prolog> 
  <conbody> 
	 <p>The following graphic represents two rules in a composite audience. 
	 </p> 
	 <p> 
		<image href="graphics/audience_sharing.png"
		 id="image_13C8A0D48ACD4E508FD173FBA273DF94"> <?xm-replace_text Paragraph?>
		</image> 
	 </p> 
	 <p>Each circle represents a rule that defines audience membership. Visitors
		that qualify as members in both audience rules overlap to become the 
		<term>defined audience</term>. 
	 </p> 
	 <note>The audience is fully defined after data collection for the specified
		period completes. 
	 </note> 
	 <p>The following example shows how to create the rules for a composite
		audience. This audience is comprised of raw 
		<keyword>Analytics</keyword> data (Home &amp; Garden section), as well as
		Chrome and Safari users (from an 
		<keyword>Analytics</keyword> segment 
		<xref
		 href="t_publish_audience_segment.xml#task_32FEEFE0B32E4E388CD4D892D727282A"
		 format="dita" scope="local">published</xref> to the 
		<keyword>Marketing Cloud</keyword>). 
	 </p> 
	 <p> 
		<image href="graphics/audience_create.png"
		 id="image_15B758E687374CDCABD3751A9BF3E55E"> <?xm-replace_text Paragraph?>
		</image> 
	 </p> 
	 <p><b>To create the combined audience</b> 
	 </p> 
	 <ul id="ul_805BC264C693412782E8888347E7826D"> 
		<li id="li_F08D45233AE241C4AC4EC1C685A47691"><xref
		  href="audience_example.xml#concept_9588E880E0C7438E8B29AC7685AD0346/section_78426ED1D40D4EF39DE26FE1065FBC89"
		  format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text 1. Navigate to the Audience Library?></xref>
		  
		</li> 
		<li id="li_7D475310A97841DC9402C4B3D44E0EFD"><xref
		  href="audience_example.xml#concept_9588E880E0C7438E8B29AC7685AD0346/section_2A4DA40D81F44551B99B2460E1E4F76E"
		  format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text 2. Create the site section rule?></xref>
		  
		</li> 
		<li id="li_7CB3B1F22BA741DD87F6C863DB1F3D10"><xref
		  href="audience_example.xml#concept_9588E880E0C7438E8B29AC7685AD0346/section_2A66A80747664DA98B7530A76C3A345F"
		  format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text 3. Create the browser rule?></xref>
		  
		</li> 
		<li id="li_757E23C2EEA54EC1B058D5F557E0FDCC"><xref
		  href="audience_example.xml#concept_9588E880E0C7438E8B29AC7685AD0346/section_349CC85F57E2481BA3B7E7ADE47D0306"
		  format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text 4. Analyze the defined audience?></xref>
		  
		</li> 
	 </ul> 
	 <section id="section_78426ED1D40D4EF39DE26FE1065FBC89"> 
		<title>1. Navigate to the Audience Library</title> 
		<p> Click 
		  <menucascade> 
			 <uicontrol>Marketing Cloud</uicontrol> 
			 <uicontrol>Profile
				Management</uicontrol><uicontrol>Audiences</uicontrol> 
		  </menucascade>, then click 
		  <uicontrol>New</uicontrol>. 
		</p> 
		<p><image href="graphics/new_audience.png"
		  id="image_803FA46960C34DDFBA8834DD2B3E615E"><?xm-replace_text Paragraph?></image>
		  
		</p> 
	 </section> 
	 <section id="section_2A4DA40D81F44551B99B2460E1E4F76E"> 
		<title>2. Create the site section rule</title> 
		<p>Under 
		  <wintitle>Rules</wintitle>, define the 
		  <term>Home &amp; Garden</term> attribute selections: 
		</p> 
		<ul id="ul_52553A6032C446F4984F342EA567BE27"> 
		  <li id="li_BEEEC7DA95B34E57A6288511FBFDCFEE"> 
			 <uicontrol>Attribute Source:</uicontrol> Raw Analytics Data 
		  </li> 
		  <li id="li_ABF106983838462FB1175EB98E6E924C"> 
			 <uicontrol>Report Suite:</uicontrol> Report Suite 31 
		  </li> 
		  <li id="li_9709D1FCC7724942A31122B950661F06">Dimension = 
			 <menucascade><uicontrol>Store (Merch)
				  (v6)</uicontrol><uicontrol>Equals</uicontrol><uicontrol>Home &amp;
				  Garden</uicontrol></menucascade> 
		  </li> 
		</ul> 
		<p> 
		  <image href="graphics/home_garden.png"
			id="image_1A30BD536FDE4B1CAB684B576977033E"> <?xm-replace_text Paragraph?>
		  </image> 
		</p> 
	 </section> 
	 <section id="section_2A66A80747664DA98B7530A76C3A345F"> 
		<title>3. Create the browser rule</title> 
		<p>The 
		  <term>Chrome &amp; Safari Visitors</term> is an audience segment shared
		  from Analytics: 
		</p> 
		<ul id="ul_AF3D6F4836E9454CBEC5F36A12DB4EE4"> 
		  <li id="li_5F137824BE32453EB9CB07C9335FDA08"> 
			 <uicontrol>Attribute Source:</uicontrol> Marketing Cloud 
		  </li> 
		  <li id="li_6E5E2FC54C6B4CF3B71FFE3C08526159"> 
			 <uicontrol>Dimension:</uicontrol> Chrome &amp; Safari Visitors 
		  </li> 
		</ul> 
		<p> 
		  <image href="graphics/chrome_safari.png"
			id="image_87246CDFCBA846E294FD9163E0C57AB3"> <?xm-replace_text Paragraph?>
		  </image> 
		</p> 
		<p>For comparison, you might add an 
		  <term>OR</term> rule to see all visitors to a site section, such as
		  Patio &amp; Furniture. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <image href="graphics/audiences_rule_patio.png"
			id="image_5BDE532B07D04F9A85E3926A2E7DF741"> <?xm-replace_text Paragraph?>
		  </image> 
		</p> 
	 </section> 
	 <section id="section_349CC85F57E2481BA3B7E7ADE47D0306"> 
		<title>4. Analyze the defined audience</title> 
		<p>The resulting rule is a defined audience comprising Chrome &amp;
		  Safari users who visited Home &amp; Garden. The Patio &amp; Furniture segment
		  provides additional insight into all visitors visiting that site section. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <image href="graphics/defined_audience.png"
			id="image_8BAA9859565C49CD83FB13D688CB053A"> <?xm-replace_text Paragraph?>
		  </image> 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <b>Historical Estimate:</b> (Dotted circle) Represents rules created
		  based on 
		  <keyword>Analytics</keyword> data. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <b>Actual Audience:</b> (Solid circle) Any rule created that has 30
		  days of data from audience management. When the audience management data
		  reaches 30 days, the line becomes solid and represents actual numbers. 
		</p> 
		<p>After the data collection completes for the specified period, the
		  circles combine to show a defined audience. 
		</p> 
	 </section> 
  </conbody> 
</concept> 
